At least 16 have been reported dead as well as dozens injured after the deadly collision. The passenger train was passing between Greek cities Thessaloniki and Larissa when it collided with a freight train just before midnight. There is a large emergency service presence at the scene near Tempi, about 235 miles north of Athens.    We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express  